The paper discusses the intersection of Computational Linguistics and Bibliometrics, which involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques applied to scientific papers. This fits well with the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
